[[div class="foundation snow"]]
[[=]]
+ ##red|!__NOTICE__!##
++ DOCUMENT WARNING SCP-042-VN
-----
**The following document[s] contain provisional explanations and/or declassified information regarding incident-related anomal[y/ies] encountered by Site-333 personnel.**


**PLEASE NOTE THAT THE DOCUMENTS BELOW ARE FUNCTIONAL EFFECTIVE ONLY IN SITE-333, AND HAVE NOT BEEN INCLUDED INTO OFFICIAL DATABASE.**
[[/=]]
[[/div]]


[[include :scp-wiki:component:anomaly-class-bar-source
|item-number= 042-VN
|clearance= 1
|container-class=esoteric
|secondary-class=thaumiel
|secondary-icon=https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/component%3Aanomaly-class-bar/thaumiel-icon.svg
|disruption-class=vlam
|risk-class=warning
]]
-----
**Special Containment Procedures:** According to a vote by the [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/integration-program-hub Integration Program], SCP-042-VN is permitted to operate outside the Veil (within limitations). The location where SCP-042-VN is active has been purchased by the SCP Foundation and placed under GoI-"Sh≈´sh≈´-In" guardianship as a front facility.


Furthermore, Site-333 Director, Vincent Bohart is to arrive at this area promptly if the anomaly requests a meeting with him.


**Description:** SCP-042-VN is the designation for an anomalous Toyota Previa. The anomaly appears to be comparable to conventional cars of the same type, with a predominantly white color. SCP-042-VN has been observed to transform its color depending on its mood at the time.


Include list of moods:
* Red - Anger
* Pink - Shy
* Black - Aloof
* White - Happy


SCP-042-VN is sapient, and is able to move independently without a driver inside.
----
**Addendum 1:** Discovery


SCP-042-VN was officially discovered on February 28, 2025, by Director Bohart when traveling to Japan during Site-333‚Äôs annual spring break, directly encountering the anomaly at Hokkaid≈ç Shrine, Sapporo City, Hokkaido.


Before Bohart's initial interaction, SCP-042-VN was known to the Foundation through its local popularity and influence, but could not be put into containment due to failed cooperative efforts with the Foundation's Japanese Branch, the operations of the GoI "Sh≈´sh≈´-In[[footnote]]A subsect of the Japanese Foundation Branch, sent to retrieve anomalies.[[/footnote]]'' in the area, and that containment efforts frequently disturbing local residents.


