The following recording was taken from Vincent Bohart's hand-held camera.


[[div class="foundation snow"]]
[[=]]
++ Summarized Approach Log 27/02/2025
-----
[[/=]]


//[The camera showed Director Bohart simple business suit, standing in a public park with a row of cherry trees in full bloom behind him.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[looking at the camera]// Hello, my viewers, today I‚Äôm going to try vlogging for the first time! And so, I will title it: ‚ÄúThis is a day in the life of a miko[[footnote]]Translator‚Äôs note: Japanese shrine maiden.[[/footnote]]‚Äù.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: So‚Ä¶ we are going to visit one of the shrines here in Japan; I heard there are some strange happenings down here‚Ä¶ rumor of a car becoming a shrine maiden or something like that. It must be some weird attraction or something, right? Let‚Äôs go check it out.


//[The video speeds up, showcasing Vincent‚Äôs train ride to Hokkaid≈ç Shrine.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[turns the camera to his face]// So now-


//[Director Bohart suddenly falls forward, causing the recording to be interrupted.]//


**Note:** Director Bohart refused to comment on what happened following the event, but it can be assumed that he fell onto the stone pathway leading up to the shrine.


[[/div]]
----
**Addendum 2:**


[[div class="foundation snow"]]
[[=]]
+++ Location Background Briefing
++++ //Hokkaid≈ç Shrine//
-----
[[/=]]
[[include component:image-block name=http://khoaigarret.wikidot.com/local--files/kirq-pic/hokkaido_shrine.jpg|width=100%|align=center|caption=Hokkaid≈ç Shrine in the winter.]]
-----
Hokkaid≈ç Shrine (ÂåóÊµ∑ÈÅìÁ•ûÂÆÆ) was designed and constructed in 1869.

Currently, the location is under the control of GoI ‚ÄúSh≈´sh≈´-In‚Äù. According to information provided by the GoI, the shrine is responsible for worshiping and preserving "soul pieces" of 4 kami[[footnote]]Kami (Deities) turn away from the world, leaving their own "traces" behind. Some left behind weapons or souvenirs that were always attached to them, others sacrificed their own bodies and dispersed throughout Heavenly Nation, waiting for their [worshippers]/[descendants] to revive. ~Excerpt from ‚ÄúSecretly use Kaleidoscope to look in Shinto‚Äù, Shinano Chuo Post.[[/footnote]], ≈åkunitama, ≈åkuninushi, Sukunahikona, and Emperor Meiji, after Professor Yutaro Morino‚Äôs [http://scp-int.wikidot.com/r-sinano-chuo-co-jp-2050-09-07-e34j876 ‚ÄúUnified Theory‚Äù] was put into testing in some provinces of Japan. Hokkaid≈ç Shrine is one of the most prestigious establishments in exorcisms, wedding ceremonies, spirit purification and other events related to Shinto.
-----
[[=]]
++++ //Kannushi//
[[include component:image-block name=https://khoaigarret.wdfiles.com/local--files/kirq-pic/kannushi.jpg|width=95%|align=center|caption=Portrait photo.]]
[[/=]]
-----
**Name:** Tanaka Hiroshi


**Background:** Hiroshi Tanaka is the fourth Kannushi descendant of Tanaka‚Äôs family. He held the role for nearly 20 years even after his wife passed away after she had her two daughters. There were many rumors related to the subject such as "having the power to uproot a giant tree" or "having the power passed down from [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abe_no_Seimei Abe no Seimei]". Besides working at the Hokkaid≈ç Shrine, the subject also participates in many volunteer activities such as donating blood, cooking free community meals for the homeless.
-----
[[/div]]
----


**Addendum 3:**


The following recording was recorded after an interval when the first one ended:


[[div class="foundation snow"]]
[[=]]
++ Summarized Approach Log 27/02/2025
-----
[[/=]]


//The recording begins with the face of Director Bohart which is scratched and has red rashes.//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[takes a breath]// Well, after more than half an hour of non-stop walking, I have reached the shrine.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Overall, the shrine is very Japanese, I mean exquisite in a Japanese style? If anyone plays Minecraft and builds some structure like this, they will understand what I‚Äôm sayin'.


[[include component:image-block name=http://khoaigarret.wikidot.com/local--files/kirq-pic/hokkaido_shrine2.jpg|width=100%|align=center|caption=Picture of Hokkaid≈ç Shrine by Bohart, taken from a tourist.]]


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Hey everyone, I see an old man over there. Looking at the outfit, from what I read online, he's the shrine manager of this place.


//[Vincent points to the courtyard, where a man disguises as a priest, is sweeping.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Now I'll go talk to him.


//[Vincent slowly approaches the man.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Hello shrine manager.


##E64019|**Tanaka Hiroshi**##: „Åô„Åø„Åæ„Åõ„Çì„ÄÅÂàÜ„Åã„Çâ„Å™„ÅÑ„Åß„Åô.[[footnote]]Translate: Sorry, I don't understand what you are saying.[[/footnote]]


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Huh? //[waves arms]// Sorry, don't understand, Japanese language? You understand, I don't know Japanese.


##E64019|**Tanaka Hiroshi**##: Forgive my joke, I do know English.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##:  Ah, that‚Äôs fine. So uh, I'm a YouTuber on my holiday. I heard that this place has a special feature: there's a car which is appointed as the shrine's miko. I want to film it, is that allowed? I'll stay just a few days to film. In return, I can help you with housework as well as attract customers. Is that okay, temple master?


##E64019|**Tanaka Hiroshi**##: Please forgive me, my dear foreign YouTuber, but Hokkaid≈ç Shrine is a sacred place so I cannot allow outsiders to stay here.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Oh my, but‚Äì but‚Äì


//[Video suddenly cuts off.]//


**Note:** According to Director Bohart, he had approached and asked the shrine manager to stay and make a documentary film about the lives of miko at the shrine under the guise of a foreign YouTuber to observe and have closer contact with the anomaly. Mr. Tanaka Hiroshi, the current shrine caretaker, consented to this request after more than three hours of discussions with Director Bohart.


**P/s 1:** Probably clung to someone's leg to beg for a free stay.‚Äì ##red|**Tony Catalano##**


**P/s 2:** Probably clung to someone's leg and wailed to beg for a free stay.‚Äì ##green|**Leonora Morales##**
[[/div]]
----
**Addendum 4:**


[[div class="foundation snow"]]
[[=]]
++ Summarized Approach Log 28/02/2025
-----
[[/=]]


//[The recording begins with a montage depicting local flora and the shrine's outskirts, with a rooster crowing audibly in the background, edited by Director Bohart as the intro.]//


//[The frame transitions to Director Bohart standing in front of bathroom mirror.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Hey guys, your beloved YouTuber - Egg-head Adventures is here. Is that a good name for this? //[Vincent laughs]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Now uh, I'm just doing a little personal hygiene. //[combs his bald head]// Being a YouTuber also requires being handsome, y'know. After I finish, imma go have breakfast and then explore this place.


//[Vincent looks at his watch.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Fuckin' hell, already ten AM? I missed my breakfast.


//[Video is interrupted by a clip from cartoon TV series SpongeBob SquarePants, displaying the words 'one hour later' accompanied by a voiceover[[footnote]]Further interviews revealed that Director Bohart deliberately included to enhance viewer engagement and save time.[[/footnote]]. Video resumes, displaying the shrine's surroundings.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[makes air quotes]// Now I'm taking a "morning" walk around this place. Since I already have my VIP ticket, I'm the only visitor here. I think the people around here all work in the shrine.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: The natural scenery here is so beautiful, but kinda it‚Äôs kinda humid here, which sucks. However, the shrine is remarkably clean, blending seamlessly in with everything. However, it‚Äôs definitely not as good as my beloved Atlantis City. //[Vincent laughs]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: There are a lot of trees here but not many leaves fall on the yard. Have to admit that those miko are very hardworking‚Äì


[[include component:image-block
name=http://khoaigarret.wikidot.com/local--files/kirq-pic/anomaly.jpg|
caption=Image taken from the camera.|
width=350px
]]


//[Director Bohart encounters a Miko with SCP-042-VN following.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[Vincent suddenly cuts himself off, whispering into the camera]// Holy shit, I caught it guys. I‚Äôll go try to talk to them!


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Konnichiwa, miku-san!


//[The Miko turns to face Bohart with a confused expression.]//


##F30474|**Miko**##: Greetings, customer.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: A-- ah, greeting-


##F30474|**Miko**##: Are there any problems?


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Y‚Äì yeah so, I see you have a car following you? I mean like, aren't vehicles banned from the shrine grounds?


##F30474|**Miko**##: //[turns back to looking at the car then covers her mouth with one hand and smiles]// Ah, no need to worry about that. Toyo is a member of our shrine.


//[SCP-042-VN beeps.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Oh, th-- that's how is it. Understood. So h‚Äì how should I address-- um Toyo-san?


##F30474|**Miko**##: Toyo is the youngest sister in our miko group here. She is the most compassionate member, despite her shyness among outsiders. You will eventually become close to her.


//[A small ‚Äú„ÅØ„ÅÑ„ÅØ„ÅÑ‚Äù[[footnote]]In Japanese. Translation: "Yes Yes"[[/footnote]] is heard from the anomaly. However, Vincent doesn‚Äôt seem to notice this. The anomaly begins to roll forward, approaching Miko from behind.]//


##F30474|**Miko**##: Oh right, we need to prepare for the afternoon ceremony and welcome other visitors, so please excuse me.


//[The Miko then walks out of sight from Vincent with the anomaly. Vincent pauses for a moment before calling out.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Ah I forgot, my name is Vincent. And you, Miss Miko?


##F30474|**Miko**##: My name is Keiko, Tanaka Keiko.


//[A muffled vocalization is audible from the anomaly's cockpit, resembling "To-yo". After that, both subjects continue walking, and before they are out of sight, the anomaly nudges Miko Keiko in the back, causing her to laugh.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[wiping sweat from his forehead]// Talking to girls these days is so stressful man.


[[/div]]
----


**Addendum 5:**


[[div class="foundation snow"]]
[[=]]
++ Summarized Approach Log 29/02/2025
-----
[[/=]]


//[The scene begins with Vincent standing and waving at the camera.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Sup guys, it‚Äôs ya boi. Yesterday we got quite a view on the miko car.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: However, I haven‚Äôt gotten close to her that much, so today's objective is to have a better look.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: For now, imma heads to the coffee shop. Might be able to get some useful information here.

[[include component:image-block name=http://khoaigarret.wikidot.com/local--files/kirq-pic/hokkaido_shrinecafe.jpg|width=100%|align=center|caption=Hokkaid≈ç Shine‚Äôs coffee shop.]]


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: This place is quite spacious, and a lot of people came to visit it also. Heading to the counter right now.


//[Vincent moves to the counter, where there is an employee currently serving. He moves to the back of the line, behind three people.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[holds and turns the camera, then starts whispering. The customer‚Äôs face has been blurred out.]// There‚Äôs lots of people here.


//[The video runs faster, skipping eight minutes of Vincent's random chat about various topics. Afterward, the line in front of Vincent is cleared out. It‚Äôs now his turn to order a drink.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: //[looks at the employee]// Hello, it is nice to see that there‚Äôs a place like this in the middle of the Hokkaid≈ç Shrine. I‚Äôm wondering if this shop was made to help the needy, because that is so wholesome and thoughtful that you guys even thought about us being uncomfortable here.


##F30474|**Employee**##: Uhh, no, we just need the money.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Oh.


//[A short pause.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: So, can I get a hot matcha latte please?


##F30474|**Employee**##: Right away sir.


//[Vincent walks and sits down at the furthest table in the corner of the room, where a man is already sitting.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: 'Sup mate, mind if I sit here?


//[In front of Vincent is a long-haired, middle-aged man with glasses.]//


##black|**Guy A**##: Oh, um, sure sir. But I‚Äôm not gonna talk with strangers.


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: Come on, man. Aren‚Äôt we the same? //[points to their head]// Well, except the hair. What‚Äôs with the ‚ÄúSir‚Äù tho?


//[Vincent grabs the coffee from the waiter and takes a sip. He then continues.]//


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: By the way, what brings you here? Visiting?


##black|**Guy A**##: Yes, to meet the manager.


[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-features-source |hover-enlarge=--]
|enlarge-amount=10
|speed=120
|float=true
|align=right
|width=18rem
|url=http://khoaigarret.wikidot.com/local--files/kirq-pic/wibu.png
|alt=alt|alt-text=
|add-caption=true
|caption=Personal photo provided by the subject.
]]


##blue|**Vincent Bohart**##: So, you‚Äôre his relatives?


